tp:treatment-sec.p:
Geographic variation.
A male and female collected in a semi-desert site near Tazenakht (
Morocco
) agree closely with the present species in external morphology and male terminalia, but the dark pattern on the mesonotum and abdomen is diminished in both sexes: Paired dark marks on tergites III and IV of the abdomen much smaller and obtusely triangular; postsutural black band on the female mesonotum (
Fig. 7D
) is further characterised by a deep hind marginal incision.
